</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Det._Robert_Goren" title="Det. Robert Goren" class="mw-redirect">Det. Robert Goren</a> (played by <a href="/wiki/Vincent_D%27Onofrio" title="Vincent D'Onofrio">Vincent D'Onofrio</a>) of <a href="/wiki/Law_%26_Order:_Criminal_Intent" title="Law &amp; Order: Criminal Intent">Law &amp; Order: Criminal Intent</a> is a criminal profiler. His mentor Dr. Declan Gage, played by <a href="/wiki/John_Glover_(actor)" title="John Glover (actor)">John Glover (actor)</a>, is known as one of the first modern-day criminal profilers, with his number one source of intrigue and claim to fame, a serial killer named Sebastian.</li>
<li>The <a href="/wiki/Kay_Scarpetta" title="Kay Scarpetta">Kay Scarpetta</a> book series (written by <a href="/wiki/Patricia_Cornwell" title="Patricia Cornwell">Patricia Cornwell</a>) also features Benson Wesley, an FBI Criminal Profiler based in <a href="/wiki/Quantico,_Virginia" title="Quantico, Virginia">Quantico, Virginia</a>. He is featured in many of the books and displays the disciplines and skills of a criminal profiler.</li>
<li>The UK television series <i><a href="/wiki/Wire_in_the_Blood" title="Wire in the Blood">Wire in the Blood</a></i> features a clinical psychologist played by <a href="/wiki/Robson_Green" title="Robson Green">Robson Green</a> who profiles serial killers. The UK television series <i><a href="/wiki/Cracker_(TV_Series)" title="Cracker (TV Series)" class="mw-redirect">Cracker</a></i> focuses on a psychologist who aids police in forming profiles and interrogating suspects.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Profiler_(TV_series)" title="Profiler (TV series)">Profiler (TV series)</a>, an <a href="/wiki/NBC" title="NBC">NBC</a> TV series, focused on a profiler whose insights manifested themselves in visions.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Criminal_Minds" title="Criminal Minds">Criminal Minds</a>, a <a href="/wiki/CBS" title="CBS">CBS</a> TV series, focuses on an FBI team who utilize profiling.</li>
</ul>
